{{Multiple issues| {{Notability|Products|date=August 2016}} {{Primary sources|date=August 2016}} }} {{Infobox software | name = Fedena | logo = Fedena SIS logo.png | logo size = 300px | screenshot =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Fedena dashboard.png|300px]] --> | caption = dashboard view of fedena 2.0 | developer = [[Foradian|Foradian Technologies]] | platform = [[Ruby on Rails]] | genre = [[Student information system]], School [[Enterprise resource planning|ERP]] | license = [[Apache License|Apache License 2.0]] | website = [http://www.fedena.com/ www.fedena.com] | latest_release_version = 3.6 | latest_release_date = {{start date and age|2017|10|18}} | latest_preview_version = | latest_preview_date = | operating_system = Any (web-based application) }}
'''Fedena''' is an [[open-source software|open-source]] [[school management software]] developed on the [[Ruby on Rails]] Framework. It is [[web 2.0]] [[web application]] developed by [[Foradian|Foradian Technologies]]. Fedena is cloud based school ERP software used in schools for administration purposes. Fedena is being used by the Education Department of [[Government of Kerala]] to automate the system and process of over 15,000 schools in the state and is named as [[Sampoorna]].<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/article2378386.ece</ref><ref>http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2862755</ref>{{User-generated inline|certain=y|date=August 2016}} Fedena is now used in more than 40,000 institutions in the world.<ref>https://finance.yahoo.com/news/fedena-free-opensource-school-management-143000390.html</ref>{{User-generated inline|certain=y|date=August 2016}}{{Failed verification|date=August 2016}} For the development and support of Fedena, Foradian won the [[TR35|MIT TR35]] 2012 India award for innovation in education domain.<ref>http://www.technologyreview.in/tr35/profile.aspx?trid=1248</ref>{{Failed verification|date=August 2016}} Fedena Pro is the commercial version of this software and comes with add-on modules or the premium modules.
The [https://github.com/projectfedena/fedena open source version] of Fedena has not seen updates since version 2.3 in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/projectfedena/fedena/releases|title=projectfedena/fedena|website=GitHub|access-date=2016-03-11}}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=August 2016}} Developed on [[Ruby on Rails]] frame work with [[Model–view–controller|MVC]] architecture. The application is composed of a basic module which satisfies all the necessary requirements of a simple [[Student information system|SIS]]. Fedena is optimized for customization and there are many add on modules which can be installed easily to extend the power and usability. Fedena is currently integrated with [[Moodle]], [[Google Apps]] and [[Tally Solutions|Tally]]. Fedena supports [[multitenant]] architecture and is used to manage group of institutions. Fedena started the development in June 2009. It is currently in Version 3.5.3 which was released in March 2017.{{Citation needed|date=March 2017}}<ref>http://www.fedena.com/blog/2017/03/styx-fedena-3-5-3-release-notes.html</ref>
The Fedena project is owned by [[Foradian Technologies]], an internet engineering company based in Bangalore, India. The company raised $2 million funding from William Bissell, Managing Director of Fabindia in April 2014.<ref>http://forbesindia.com/blog/business-strategy/william-bissell-the-angel-investor-is-scaling-up/</ref> Foradian initiated and successfully implemented Fedena in the state of Kerala for all the government schools. The project was named as [[Sampoorna]]. The project was implemented in coordination with the Education Department of Government of Kerala, India to automate the system and process of over 15,000 schools in the state.{{Citation needed|date=August 2016}}
