The '''Ibom [[Digital library|E-Library]]'''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/03/e-library-places-uyo-at-advantage-says-gov-akpabio/|title=E-Library places Uyo at advantage, says Gov Akpabio - Vanguard News|date=2013-03-20|newspaper=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-16}}</ref> is a [[library]] located in [[Uyo]], [[Akwa Ibom State|Akwa Ibom State, Nigeria.]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.breakingnews.com/topic/akwa-ibom-nigeria/|title=Breaking news on Akwa Ibom, Nigeria|newspaper=breakingnews.com|access-date=2016-12-16}}</ref> The library is the first of its kind in [[West Africa]].{{cn|date=December 2016}} Ibom E-Library was built on September 25, 2007, by [[Akwa Ibom State Government]] under the leadership of [[Godswill Akpabio]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.informationng.com/2015/12/8-things-you-didnt-know-about-godswill-akpabio.html|title=8 Things You Didn’t Know About Godswill Akpabio|date=2015-12-13|website=INFORMATION NIGERIA|access-date=2016-12-16}}</ref> and commissioned by [[President of Nigeria|Nigerian President]] in July 27, 2012.
The E-Library has a multi-functional Conference centre used for conferences and summits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mmanti-umoh/why-should-everyone-atten_b_10866858.html|title=Why Should Everyone Attend Akwa Ibom Economic Summit #AES2016|last=Management|first=Mmanti Umoh Education|last2=Development|first2=Youth Leadership|date=2016-07-08|website=The Huffington Post|access-date=2016-12-16|last3=Consultancy|first3=Image|last4=save|first4=Idea Developer I. leave No stone unturned to|last5=Africa|first5=serve}}</ref> The Library also accommodates small [[Startup company|startups]] as an incubation system.
