'''R. John M. Hughes''' (born {{birth date and age|1958|7|15|df=y}}) is a Swedish [[computer scientist]] and professor in the department of Computing Science at the [[Chalmers University of Technology]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chalmers.se/en/staff/Pages/rjmh.aspx|title=Chalmers Staff Page|last=|first=|date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

==Contributions==
In 1984, Hughes received his PhD from the University of Oxford for the thesis "The Design and Implementation of Programming Languages".<ref>
{{Citation
| title = THE DESIGN AND IMPLEMENTATION OF PROGRAMMING LANGUAGES
| url = https://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/files/3309/PRG40.pdf
| accessdate = November 7, 2018
| publisher  = University of Oxford
| publication-date = July 1983
}}
</ref>

Hughes is a member of the Functional Programming group at Chalmers, and much of his research relates to the [[Haskell programming language]]. He does research in the field of [[programming languages]] and is the author of many influential research papers on the subject, including "Why Functional Programming Matters".<ref>{{Cite journal | last = Hughes | first = John | title = Why Functional Programming Matters | journal = Computer Journal | volume = 32 | issue = 2 | pages = 98–107 | year = 1989| url = http://www.cse.chalmers.se/~rjmh/Papers/whyfp.html | accessdate = 2010-05-06 | doi=10.1093/comjnl/32.2.98}}</ref>

Hughes is one of the developers of [[QuickCheck]], as well as cofounder and CEO of [[QuviQ]], which provides the QuickCheck software and offers classes in how to use it.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}

In 2016 he appeared in the [[popular science]] YouTube channel Computerphile explaining Functional Programming and QuickCheck.<ref>{{Citation|last=Computerphile|title=Functional Programming & Haskell - Computerphile|date=2016-11-30|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LnX3B9oaKzw|accessdate=2018-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Computerphile|title=Code Checking Automation - Computerphile|date=2017-01-18|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AfaNEebCDos|accessdate=2018-01-11}}</ref>

