}}'''Shishu Niketan Higher Secondary School''' was established in 1984.

== Description ==
Shishu Niketan Higher Secondary School is located in Jirania, West Tripura. There are 52 dedicated and professional faculty members who impart quality education to children in this State Board school.

This school’s primary medium of instruction is Bengali and the student teacher ratio is 26:1. The school takes pride of its excellent teaching methodology.

Students from 1 to 12 are taught in this school. This school has approximately 1356 as student strength. This school’s library has 200 books.

The school has given exceptional results in the academic sphere and its students have excelled in extra co-curricular activities too. The perentage of students passing the exam is 100% with 61% scoring first grade.{{Reflist}}

