'''Terēzija Broka''', also known as Terēze Broka, (September 30, 1925 in [[Viļāni]] parish, [[Latvia]] – October 22, 2018) was a Latvian conductor, educator and culture worker.<ref name="eng.lsm.lv">{{cite news |title=Renowned conductor passes away aged 93 |url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/culture/culture/renowned-conductor-passes-away-aged-93.a297011/ |accessdate=26 October 2018 |publisher=[[Public Broadcasting of Latvia]] |date=23 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="Diena-23Oct2018">{{cite news |title=Mūžībā devusies Dziesmu un deju svētku Goda virsdiriģente Terēzija Broka |url=https://www.diena.lv/raksts/kd/muzika/muziba-devusies-dziesmu-un-deju-svetku-goda-virsdirigente-terezija-broka-14207441 |accessdate=26 October 2018 |work=Diena |date=23 October 2018 |language=lv}}</ref><ref name="LA.lv-23Oct2018">{{cite news |title=In Memoriam. Mūžībā devusies pazīstamā diriģente Terēzija Broka |url=http://www.la.lv/in-memoriam-muziba-devusies-pazistama-dirigente-terezija-broka |accessdate=26 October 2018 |work=LA.lv |date=23 October 2018 |language=lv}}</ref> Broka was awarded the [[Order of the Three Stars]] in 1995 for promotion of [[Latgale|Latgalian]] culture.<ref name="DELFI-4May2017">{{cite news |title=‘Trešā zvaigzne zvaigznājā...' 13 diži latgalieši kopš 1917. gada |url=http://www.delfi.lv/kultura/news/culturenvironment/tresa-zvaigzne-zvaigznaja-13-dizi-latgaliesi-kops-1917-gada.d?id=48794501&page=9 |accessdate=26 October 2018 |work=DELFI Kultūra |date=4 May 2017 |language=lv}}</ref> Broka was chief conductor in three successive [[Latvian Song and Dance Festival]]s.<ref name="eng.lsm.lv" />

